    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f90dde31_6f301550",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-22T19:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this should be refactored to maintain the invariant: \"if the entity exists, then the account also exists\". I.e. if the entity is missing, we should attempt to create the account (expecting it may exist already). Then \u0027Created\u0027 field is not needed (and I believe it doesn\u0027t work currently anyway, since it is impossible to end up with ScopedIdentity entity with Created false in the datastore).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2204faae_460acbd0",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 1307247
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-24T02:31:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Update the code.\n\nIt is not intending to create the service account if \"CreationTimestamp\" is 0\nIf the service account already exists, it is \"imported\"\nBroke up the transaction towards a more optimistic solution.",
      "parentUuid": "f90dde31_6f301550",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "378b6747_cd41744d",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 122,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-22T19:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "note: transaction is not a critical section. Multiple callers can end up here at the same time, and later collide trying to commit the change (only one will succeed).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 122,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a041bf98_6a3734f6",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 126,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-22T19:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not correct, err can be \"Deadline error\" or some other random crap. Compare to ds.ErrNoSuchEntity instead. If it is not nil and not ds.ErrNoSuchEntity, return err right away, it will trigger transaction retry.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 126,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 126,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "83e98c36_297d7ed8",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 126,
      "author": {
        "id": 1307247
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-24T02:31:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Refactored the whole function. PTAL.",
      "parentUuid": "a041bf98_6a3734f6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 126,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 126,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5ba4a884_3cced18e",
        "filename": "tokenserver/appengine/impl/utils/projectscope/storage.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-22T19:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Holding transaction while calling an external service is an antipattern. Under non-trivial QPS this will cause many requests entering the transaction body, all issuing CreateAccount RPC call, and then colliding trying to save the entity.\n\nNon trivial QPS is quite possible here, e.g. when someone makes a config change that enables a ton of LUCI Scheduler jobs in a new project.\n\nAlso, entering a transaction just to check that the entry exists is slow.\n\nA better approach would be:\n\n1. Do s.Get() outside the transaction.\n2. If missing, do CreateAccount outside the transaction. Expect that the account may already exists.\n3. On success OR on \"already exists\", transactionally create the entity (or just overwrite it, it is static).\n\nAt very least, check with Get() outside the transaction first.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 131,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 131,
        "endChar": 74
      },
      "revId": "d37aa2a64e46b133499bb31a0260d76f6a9b6818",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
